From 97bc723492147ad0871448f771a06a5c538d2704 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Razer Phone 2 Linux Maintainers <razerphone2linux@localhost>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 14:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: qcom-cci: use factory transaction retries

The Razer SDM845 downstream camera stack programs a retry count of three in
bits 16-17 of every CCI I2C SET_PARAM command.  The mainline CCI driver leaves
these bits at zero, so a transient first NACK immediately fails sensor probe.

Program the same hardware retry count for CCI reads and writes.  This matches
the downstream controller transaction rather than adding a sensor-specific
software retry loop.

Signed-off-by: Razer Phone 2 Linux Maintainers <razerphone2linux@localhost>
---
 drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-qcom-cci.c | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-qcom-cci.c b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-qcom-cci.c
index f3ccfbbc4bea..4a7b5f1ce102 100644
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-qcom-cci.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-qcom-cci.c
@@ -77,6 +77,10 @@
 #define CCI_I2C_READ		10
 
 #define CCI_I2C_REPORT_IRQ_EN	BIT(8)
+#define CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM_RETRIES_SHIFT	16
+#define CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM_RETRIES	3
+#define CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM_RETRY_BITS					\
+	(CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM_RETRIES << CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM_RETRIES_SHIFT)
 
 enum {
 	I2C_MODE_STANDARD,
@@ -344,7 +348,8 @@ static int cci_i2c_read(struct cci *cci, u16 master,
 	if (ret < 0)
 		return ret;
 
-	val = CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM | (addr & 0x7f) << 4;
+	val = CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM | (addr & 0x7f) << 4 |
+	      CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM_RETRY_BITS;
 	writel(val, cci->base + CCI_I2C_Mm_Qn_LOAD_DATA(master, queue));
 
 	val = CCI_I2C_READ | len << 4;
@@ -397,7 +402,8 @@ static int cci_i2c_write(struct cci *cci, u16 master,
 	if (ret < 0)
 		return ret;
 
-	val = CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM | (addr & 0x7f) << 4;
+	val = CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM | (addr & 0x7f) << 4 |
+	      CCI_I2C_SET_PARAM_RETRY_BITS;
 	writel(val, cci->base + CCI_I2C_Mm_Qn_LOAD_DATA(master, queue));
 
 	load[i++] = CCI_I2C_WRITE | len << 4;
-- 
2.51.0
